  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Tax justice for equitable health care</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Name of project: Progressive domestic resources mobilization, allocation and use for equitable health care in VietnamCountry: VietnamProject goal: #Empowered civil society (CSOs, CBOs and communities) capable to effectively influence on: i) Progressive taxation (particularly reducing harmful tax exemption and incentives ) to increase domestic resource mobilisation, especially for local healthfacilities, and ii) More sufficient, transparent and accountable  budget allocation and spending for health services#Project results: a) A multi-stakeholder coalition is strengthened and capable to advocate for progressive/fairer taxation and efficient budget allocation and spending on health services; b) Empowered citizens are aware of and claim for their rights astax payers, with support from the coalition; and c) Robust evidence on the regression of a number of tax policies (particularly harmful tax exemption and incentives) and transparent and efficient budget allocation and spending for local health services are generated and used for advocacy bythe Coalition and empowered CBOs./ Project Counterpart:Partnership for Action on Health Equity (PAHE), an alliance of Vietnamese NGOs, established in 2009 with the mission of building and advocating for constructive voices of the civil society on critical issues of health equity facing Vietnam&apos;s health system.  &quot;</narrative>
  </description>
